  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations. In the United States, key laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Implement customer due diligence\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Conduct background checks\n5. Prevent financial crimes\n\nInternationally, the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets global standards for combating money laundering.",
